From: vyos-ls1046a-build maintainers
Subject: [PATCH] system_option: skip kexec on LS1046A (SDK QBMan cannot survive kexec)

The LS1046A Mono Gateway uses the NXP SDK staging DPAA1 stack
(drivers/staging/fsl_qbman + drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/sdk_dpaa).
Unlike mainline drivers/soc/fsl/qbman, the SDK driver has no
bman_requires_cleanup() / qman_requires_cleanup() reset path. After a
kexec, the second kernel finds BMan/QMan frame queues still configured
in CCSR from the first kernel and qman_init_fq() returns -EIO for the
first three FQs it touches, leaving 3 of 5 DPAA ports unusable
(symptom: "fsl_dpa soc:fsl,dpaa:ethernet@N: qman_init_fq(...) = -5",
"probe of soc:fsl,dpaa:ethernet@N failed with error -5").

system_option.py uses kexec to apply MANAGED_PARAM kernel cmdline
changes (hugepages, panic, mitigations, isolcpus, ...) without a cold
reboot. On LS1046A this workflow is incompatible with the SDK driver,
so we suppress the kexec self-heal branch entirely.

Behavior:
  * boot, LS1046A:        silently skip kexec. The just-booted kernel
                          is the right one; the user already cold-rebooted.
                          No Warning() is emitted at boot time, which
                          avoids any chance of configd elevating it
                          during the boot-config-loader transaction
                          (previous revision of this patch raised a
                          Warning here, which appears to have correlated
                          with an empty running-config tree on first
                          boot of a fresh ISO image).
  * post-boot, LS1046A:   emit the upstream "save and reboot" warning
                          (same path upstream takes on
                          boot_configuration_complete()==True).
  * boot, non-LS1046A:    upstream kexec self-heal — unchanged.
  * post-boot, non-LS1046A: upstream warning — unchanged.

Detection uses /proc/device-tree/compatible == 'fsl,ls1046a'.

Picked up automatically by bin/ci-setup-vyos1x.sh (globs
data/vyos-1x-*.patch).

--- a/src/conf_mode/system_option.py
+++ b/src/conf_mode/system_option.py
@@ -453,9 +453,23 @@
 
 
 def apply(options):
+    # LS1046A SDK DPAA1 cannot survive kexec: drivers/staging/fsl_qbman has
+    # no bman_requires_cleanup() / qman_requires_cleanup() equivalent of
+    # mainline drivers/soc/fsl/qbman, so the second kernel finds frame
+    # queues already configured in CCSR and qman_init_fq() returns -EIO,
+    # disabling 3 of 5 DPAA Ethernet ports. Detect this platform via the
+    # device-tree compatible string and gate out the boot-time kexec
+    # branch entirely; the post-boot Warning() path is left intact.
+    _ls1046a = False
+    try:
+        with open('/proc/device-tree/compatible', 'rb') as _f:
+            _ls1046a = b'fsl,ls1046a' in _f.read()
+    except OSError:
+        pass
+
     kexec_required, cmdline_new = generate_cmdline_for_kexec(options)
     if kexec_required:
-        if not boot_configuration_complete() and os.getenv('VYOS_CONFIGD'):
+        if (not _ls1046a) and not boot_configuration_complete() and os.getenv('VYOS_CONFIGD'):
             cmd(
                 'kexec -l /boot/vmlinuz --initrd=/boot/initrd.img '
                 f'--command-line="{cmdline_new}" --kexec-file-syscall'